thread.title: Cowboys set to launch the Matt Cassel era
thread.title_full: Cowboys set to launch the Matt Cassel era | New York Post

author: Justin Terranova
title: Cowboys set to launch the Matt Cassel era
text:
The Cowboys are getting desperate.
Dallas has lost three straight since Tony Romo broke his clavicle in Week 2, and the team will bench quarterback Brandon Weeden for Matt Cassel when they return from a bye to play the Giants in Week 7, according to an ESPN report.
Weeden has been steady but unspectacular, unable to move the ball down the field with the Cowboys (2-3) also missing star receiver Dez Bryant. Weeden has lost 11 straight starts dating to his tenure with the Browns.
Cassel, whose career launched as an injury fill-in for Tom Brady, was traded from the Bills to the Cowboys for a 2017 fifth-round pick after Romo went down.
